<h1>Portus Home Dashboard</h1>
<div class="stepText">
<p>
	Portus Home Dashboard is a customer portal offering that allows utilities to implement comprehensive realtime energy dashboards for their smart meter customers for access over the web.
</p>
<br>
</div>

<div id="column_container">
    <div id="right_column">
	<h2 class="green" style="text-align: left;">
	Energy cost, usage and CO2 footprint at your customers fingertips
	</h2>
      <p>The most important information for your customers is displayed in 4 always present summary slots at the top of each page, providing the cost, consumption, CO2 emission and trend for the current time period.<br />
      </p>
    </div>
    <div id="center_column">
      <p><img src="/images/CostSlot.jpg" /></p>
    </div>
  </div>
<br>


<div id="column_container">
    <div id="right_column">
	<h2 class="green" style="text-align: left;">
	View the consumption of the home and individual appliances
	</h2>
      <p>Customers can access the home meter and appliances being monitored in their home through the dashboard. If a Home Area Network is installed, each connected appliances can be selected and its consumption viewed separately by the customer. An 'ALL' view also shows the consumption histories of all loads simultaneously.<br />
      </p>
    </div>
    <div id="center_column">
      <p><img src="/images/Appliances.jpg" /></p>
    </div>
  </div>
<br>


<div id="column_container">
    <div id="right_column">
	<h2 class="green" style="text-align: left;">
	Zoom consumption histories over any period down to minute by minute
	</h2>
      <p>Consumption is generally recorded on a minute by minute basis for both the home meter and each monitored appliance. Customers can zoom consumption histories for from month to week to day, right down to hour and  minute zoom levels.<br />
      </p>
    </div>
    <div id="center_column">
      <p><img src="/images/Zoom.jpg" /></p>
    </div>
  </div>
<br>

<div id="column_container">
    <div id="right_column">
	<h2 class="green" style="text-align: left;">
	Comparisons by time period, neighbourhood or subscribed groups
	</h2>
      <p>For each appliances and their home as a whole, customers can compare current consumption with the same time in the previous period, or against the average for their neighbourhood, or they can even compare against the average of a customer group they have subscribed to.<br />
      </p>
    </div>
    <div id="center_column">
      <p><img src="/images/Meter-1.jpg" /></p>
    </div>
  </div>
<br>


<div id="column_container">
